  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a prospective, multi-centre, pragmatic randomized controlled trial to compare both
      the clinical effectiveness and cost-effectiveness of collagenase injections (CI) versus
      limited palmar fasciectomy (LPF) to determine if collagenase is a superior treatment in terms
      of improved quality of life and reducing recurrence of the disease without serious
      complications. Since collagenase injections are costly it is also important to know if this
      novel intervention is cost-effective from the patient, Ministry of Health and societal
      perspectives.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
